title: Quake of magnitude 6.3 strikes off Russia's Kurile Islands: USGS - International - World
text:
Related 6.6-magnitude quake sparks panic in Indonesia's Papua; no Tsunami warning Quake of 6.5 magnitude shakes Chile capital Powerful Chile quake kills at least five, 1 million evacuated An earthquake of magnitude 6.3 struck 226 km (140 miles) south of Russia's Kurile Islands on Wednesday, the United States Geological Survey reported.
There were no immediate reports of damage or casalties from the earthquake, which occurred at a depth of 34 km, off the town of Severo-Kurilsk.
